üìÑ Attachment 1 ‚Äî One-Page System Overview (MANDATORY)

File name:

RAF-GS_System_Overview.pdf

CONTENT (COPY EXACTLY)
Response-Aware Follow-Up Gating System (RAF-GS)

Author: Santhosh Guntupalli

Problem Addressed

Most CRM and workflow automation systems rely on static timers and loosely-coupled rules, leading to redundant outreach, state inconsistency, and poor response handling when inbound engagement occurs after outbound messages.

System Objective

RAF-GS is designed to enforce deterministic, response-aware decision-making for lead engagement workflows, ensuring outbound actions are gated based on explicit state, elapsed time, and inbound responses.

Core Methodology

Lead engagement is modeled as a finite state machine (FSM) with persisted state.

All outreach eligibility decisions are evaluated by a pure decision engine, independent of execution channels.

The system enforces response-aware suppression, automatically blocking outbound actions when inbound engagement occurs.

Each decision produces an audit-grade explanation, enabling traceability and evaluation.

Key States

NEW ‚Äî Lead created, no outbound contact

CONTACTED ‚Äî Outbound contact sent, awaiting response or time eligibility

ENGAGED ‚Äî Inbound response received; follow-ups suppressed

PAUSED ‚Äî Manual suspension of automation

CLOSED ‚Äî Terminal state; no actions permitted

Why This Is Architecturally Different

Unlike conventional automation logic embedded directly in workflow scripts, RAF-GS centralizes decision authority into a deterministic engine with explicit state transitions, making the system predictable, auditable, and resistant to automation drift.

